export const CITY_PRODUCT_PARAGRAPHS: Record<string, string> = {

  // ─── SAN DIEGO ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  'san-diego:roller-shades': `Mission Hills craftsman bungalows were built for a gentler era of California sun — but today's UV index is a different animal, and those original single-pane windows let in far more solar radiation than the woodwork can take. Custom roller shades have become one of the most practical upgrades in the neighborhood because they slot cleanly into the window frame without disturbing the architectural character. iL Progetto LLC carries light-filtering, room-darkening, and full-blackout fabric options, each cut to the millimeter for your specific sash dimensions. With 266 sunny days a year in San Diego, even a quality light-filtering fabric blocks up to 99% of UV before it reaches floors, rugs, or furniture. Call (858) 338-1678 to schedule your free in-home measurement.`,

  'san-diego:zebra-shades': `In North Park's mid-century bungalows and renovated duplexes, natural light is the whole point — residents open the blinds and want the room to feel alive, not cave-like. Zebra shades thread that needle precisely: alternating sheer and solid bands shift as you raise or lower the shade, dialing the room between full ambient diffusion and complete privacy without ever going dark. Because North Park interiors tend toward warm wood floors and concrete counters, zebra shades in warm ivory and greige tones integrate effortlessly. San Diego's year-round UV is relentless, so the opaque bands also serve as a UV filter when aligned. iL Progetto measures and installs custom zebra shades across every San Diego neighborhood — call (858) 338-1678 for a free consultation.`,

  'san-diego:cellular-shades': `Pacific Beach beach cottages sit close together on narrow lots, and the afternoon west exposure through a single-pane picture window can turn a living room into a greenhouse by 3 p.m. Cellular honeycomb shades address that problem structurally: each hexagonal air pocket traps a layer of insulating air between the glass and your interior, measurably reducing heat transfer without blocking the natural light that makes cottage living pleasant. Double-cell construction adds a second insulating layer for windows that take the full force of San Diego's 266 sunny days. iL Progetto LLC installs cellular shades across Pacific Beach, Mission Hills, and every San Diego neighborhood, with cordless and motorized lift options that keep cords away from children. Call (858) 338-1678 to book your free in-home energy consultation.`,

  'san-diego:roman-shades': `Mission Valley's ranch homes were designed with generous room proportions and wide windows that reward a tailored window treatment — not a roller shade, not a simple blind, but something with real fabric presence. Roman shades fold into clean horizontal pleats when raised and hang as a flat, structured panel when lowered, bringing architectural weight to windows that otherwise feel bare. In a Mission Valley great room with warm tile floors and painted cabinets, a flat linen Roman shade in a coordinating neutral becomes part of the room's design story rather than just a sun blocker. iL Progetto sources fabric in hundreds of designer options and adds optional blackout lining for bedrooms. San Diego's year-round UV calls for a UV-stable lining regardless of fabric choice. Reach us at (858) 338-1678.`,

  'san-diego:wood-aluminum-blinds': `The craftsman bungalows of Mission Hills have original hardwood floors and warm wood trim that deserve window treatments built from the same material vocabulary. Real wood blinds in a honey oak or cherry stain extend that warmth to the window plane while delivering the most precise light control of any treatment — tilt the slats to any angle from fully open to completely closed, catching or deflecting San Diego's intense afternoon light exactly as you want it. iL Progetto carries 2-inch and 2.5-inch slat widths in real wood and premium faux wood for rooms with higher humidity. Every blind is custom-cut to your window dimensions and installed by our licensed team. North Park, Pacific Beach, and Mission Hills are all in our regular service rotation. Call (858) 338-1678 to schedule your free measurement.`,

  'san-diego:shangri-la-shades': `San Diego living rooms earn their keep as multi-purpose spaces — morning coffee, afternoon work-from-home, evening entertaining — and the light management demands shift dramatically through each. Shangri-La shades answer all of them from a single mechanism: two sheer fabric facings suspend horizontal fabric vanes that tilt from full-open diffusion to closed privacy, with infinite positions between. In a North Park or Mission Hills living room with consistent southwest exposure, that flexibility means you stop chasing the sun manually across the day. The vane construction also creates genuine visual depth that a flat roller or blind simply cannot — appropriate for rooms where the window treatment is a design statement. iL Progetto installs Shangri-La shades across San Diego with motorized options available. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'san-diego:curtains-drapery': `Across Pacific Beach and Mission Hills, homeowners who have lived through cheap vertical blinds and off-the-shelf panels understand the difference custom drapery makes. Floor-to-ceiling panels in a quality linen or cotton-linen blend change the ceiling height, soften acoustics, and anchor a room in a way that no functional shade can replicate. iL Progetto designs, sources, and installs custom panel drapery on precision metal track systems — ripple-fold for contemporary interiors, pinch-pleat for traditional rooms — with optional blackout lining behind any front fabric. San Diego's year-round UV means every set of drapery we install includes a UV-stable lining regardless of fabric weight. Panels are fabricated to your exact floor-to-ceiling measurement, not a standard catalog length. Call (858) 338-1678 for a design consultation.`,

  'san-diego:motorized-shading': `San Diego is one of the most consistently sunny cities in the United States, which means light management is not a seasonal chore — it is a daily one. Motorized shading takes that chore off the list entirely: program your shades to raise at sunrise, lower to a protective position at peak UV hours, and open again at sunset, all without touching a remote or opening an app. iL Progetto installs motorized systems compatible with Alexa, Google Home, and Apple HomeKit across Mission Hills, North Park, Pacific Beach, and the broader San Diego market. Whether you are automating a single living room window or a whole-home system across multiple floors, our installer handles all programming at the installation appointment. Battery and hardwired motors both available. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'san-diego:plantation-shutters': `Few window treatments are as well-matched to San Diego's architectural range as plantation shutters. In Mission Hills craftsman bungalows they echo original wood detailing; in Mission Valley ranch homes they add the permanent, built-in feel that distinguishes an owned home from a rental. Custom-built plantation shutters are classified as a permanent home improvement at resale — they return value in a way no shade or curtain does. Wide 4.5-inch louvres tilt smoothly to manage San Diego's year-round UV intensity, and the hardwood frame seals the window perimeter completely, eliminating the edge gaps where light bleeds past a roller shade. iL Progetto's shutters are built to your exact window dimensions and installed by our licensed team — CA License #1127055. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'san-diego:faux-wood-blinds': `Mission Valley's ranch homes and Pacific Beach's beach cottages share one common challenge: west-facing windows that bake in afternoon sun for six to eight hours every day. Real wood blinds warp under that sustained thermal cycling within a few seasons; faux wood blinds do not. The composite construction is dimensionally stable across San Diego's temperature range, UV-resistant, and moisture-proof for bathroom and kitchen applications. Visually, the difference from real wood is negligible at normal viewing distance — warm matte finishes in golden oak, espresso, and white coordinate with virtually any interior palette. iL Progetto cuts every blind to your exact window width and drop, eliminating the edge gaps that standard-size products leave. Call (858) 338-1678 for a free in-home measurement.`,

  'san-diego:aluminum-blinds': `Not every San Diego window needs a luxury solution. Garages, home offices, rental units, and utility rooms in North Park and Mission Valley call for a treatment that is durable, affordable, and genuinely effective at light control without demanding design attention it doesn't deserve. Custom aluminum blinds fill that role precisely — powder-coated slats resist San Diego's persistent UV without fading, and the slim 1-inch profile stacks nearly flat when fully raised. Coastal homeowners in Pacific Beach appreciate that powder-coated aluminum handles salt air better than wood or fabric alternatives. iL Progetto cuts every aluminum blind to your exact window dimensions and installs with cordless options for child safety. No standard-size compromises. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'san-diego:vertical-blinds': `San Diego's indoor-outdoor lifestyle defines the architecture of Mission Valley ranch homes and Pacific Beach cottages alike — wide sliding glass doors to patios and yards are standard, not special. Vertical blinds remain the most functional solution for those openings: the louvres stack completely clear of the door track when fully open, and tilt to any angle for light control and privacy when closed. Contemporary fabric louvres in linen and woven textures bear no resemblance to the vinyl vertical blinds of the 1990s — they drape softly and coordinate with modern interiors. iL Progetto installs custom vertical blinds sized to your exact door or window width across every San Diego neighborhood. Motorized traverse options are available for frequently used doors. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'san-diego:panel-track-blinds': `Open-plan living rooms in North Park and Mission Hills conversions have a window problem that traditional blinds never solve cleanly: a 10-foot wall of glass requires a window treatment that moves at the architectural scale of the opening, not one panel at a time. Panel track blinds traverse on an overhead rail, presenting wide fabric panels that cover the opening as a unified composition when closed and stack completely to one side when open. The effect reads as intentional interior design rather than a functional add-on — appropriate for rooms where the window wall is a primary feature. iL Progetto installs panel tracks in sheer, light-filtering, and blackout fabrics, with motorized track available. Call (858) 338-1678 to schedule a consultation.`,

  'san-diego:woven-wood-shades': `Pacific Beach interiors have always lived somewhere between the ocean and the living room — rattan chairs, whitewashed wood, linen throws, and natural materials that blur the line between inside and outside. Woven wood shades made from bamboo, sea grass, and jute belong in that vocabulary completely. They filter San Diego's intense coastal light through an organic weave that throws warm patterns on the floor and walls rather than blocking the sun mechanically. Every shade is custom-woven and custom-measured for your specific windows, with optional lining for bedrooms requiring more privacy. iL Progetto carries bamboo, jute, and sea grass weaves and installs across Pacific Beach, Mission Hills, and all San Diego neighborhoods. The phone is (858) 338-1678.`,

  'san-diego:sheer-shades': `In Mission Hills craftsman homes where original windows look out onto mature street trees and neighboring bungalows, the challenge is rarely keeping light out — it is managing it. Sheer shades scatter incoming San Diego sunlight across the room in diffused, even illumination that eliminates harsh glare on screens and upholstery without darkening the space. Daytime privacy is an added benefit: the sheer fabric's exterior brightness prevents passersby from seeing in while still reading clearly as a window from inside. At 266 sunny days per year, San Diego rooms benefit year-round from the UV filtration that even a light sheer fabric provides. iL Progetto installs custom sheer shades across Mission Hills, North Park, and every San Diego neighborhood. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'san-diego:blackout-curtains': `San Diego's reputation as a sunny paradise is exactly what makes blackout curtains essential for anyone who works night shifts, travels across time zones, has young children who nap, or simply prizes sleep quality. Two hundred and sixty-six sunny days a year means bright mornings every single morning — an off-the-shelf room-darkening shade with edge gaps is no match for a California sunrise at 5:47 a.m. iL Progetto's custom blackout curtains use triple-pass blackout lining fabricated behind any designer front fabric you choose, sealed to your exact window dimensions with minimal edge gaps. The result is a treatment that performs as a true blackout and looks exactly like elegant drapery from the room side. Serving Mission Hills, North Park, Pacific Beach, and all of San Diego. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'san-diego:sheer-drapes': `Formal living rooms and primary suites in Mission Hills craftsman homes are among the most beautiful residential spaces in San Diego — high ceilings, original built-ins, and windows that fill with morning and afternoon light. Sheer drapes complete those spaces in the way that no roller shade can: floor-to-ceiling panels in fine Belgian linen or voile diffuse San Diego's intense UV into a warm, scattered glow that flatters the woodwork and makes the room feel larger than it is. iL Progetto custom-cuts every panel to your exact ceiling height, installs on precision metal track or decorative rod, and handles all hardware at the appointment. Sheer drapes pair naturally with a functional blackout roller behind for night privacy. Serving all San Diego neighborhoods. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'san-diego:motorized-exterior': `San Diego's west-facing rooms take direct afternoon sun from roughly noon until sunset — a six-hour thermal assault that interior treatments fight at a disadvantage because the heat has already crossed the glass. Motorized exterior shades solve the problem at the source, deploying a UV-stable mesh screen on the outside of the window before solar energy enters the building. The result is up to 15 degrees of interior temperature reduction and a measurable drop in cooling load. iL Progetto specifies commercial-grade hardware rated for coastal UV and salt-air exposure across Pacific Beach and Mission Hills, with wind sensors for automatic retraction during Santa Ana events. App, remote, and schedule automation included. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'san-diego:sun-screens': `San Diego homeowners with canyon views, pool yards, or ocean sightlines face a specific dilemma: they want the connection to the outdoors but cannot live with the glare and UV that come through unprotected glass at peak afternoon hours. Solar sun screens resolve that conflict without sacrificing the view. A 5% openness mesh allows a clear outward sightline while reducing solar heat gain by 75–85% and cutting glare to a comfortable level for television viewing and computer work. iL Progetto installs sun screens in openness factors from 1% to 10% across Mission Hills, North Park, Pacific Beach, and Mission Valley, with cordless, chain-drive, and motorized lift options. Call (858) 338-1678 for a free in-home consultation.`,

  'san-diego:awnings': `San Diego's year-round outdoor living culture means patios and decks are not seasonal amenities — they are daily-use living spaces that need shade management as much as the interior does. A motorized retractable awning extends the livable area of a North Park or Pacific Beach bungalow into the backyard without permanently blocking skylight when retracted. Commercial-grade Sunbrella fabric resists San Diego's UV without fading, and the motorized aluminum arm system retracts completely in under 30 seconds when not needed. Wind sensors protect the mechanism during Santa Ana gusts. iL Progetto measures, fabricates, and installs custom retractable awnings across all San Diego neighborhoods. Call (858) 338-1678 for a free patio assessment.`,

  // ─── POWAY ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  'poway:roller-shades': `Poway's inland valley location means the marine layer that moderates coastal temperatures never arrives — Garden Road and Twin Peaks neighborhoods absorb the full force of Southern California summer with afternoon highs routinely pushing past 100°F. Custom roller shades with a high-openness solar mesh fabric block 80–90% of solar heat before it crosses the glass, letting in diffused light without the temperature spike that unprotected windows cause. iL Progetto carries blackout, light-filtering, and solar mesh roller fabrics custom-cut for Poway's specific window sizes — the ranch homes and two-story builds of Old Poway and Silverset have standard proportions that our system handles efficiently. Cordless and motorized options available. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'poway:zebra-shades': `Twin Peaks and Silverset homes tend toward open floor plans with great rooms that flow from kitchen to living to dining — spaces where light levels need to shift through the day without anyone manually adjusting every shade independently. Zebra shades in these rooms handle the morning light one way and the punishing Poway afternoon sun another way, all from a single mechanism. The alternating sheer and solid band construction lets you park the shade at a position that diffuses direct sunlight during peak heat hours while keeping the room bright enough for daily activity. iL Progetto installs custom zebra shades across Poway with motorized options for multi-room automation. At 95–105°F summer highs, Poway benefits from motorized schedules tied to peak sun hours. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'poway:cellular-shades': `No window treatment handles Poway's inland heat more effectively than cellular honeycomb shades. The hexagonal air pockets trap a thermal buffer between the glass and your interior that measurably reduces heat transfer — with double-cell construction adding a second insulating layer for west and south-facing windows that take the brunt of Poway's 95–105°F summers. Garden Road and Old Poway ranch homes from the 1970s and '80s were built before energy efficiency was a design priority, and single-pane or older double-pane windows in those homes benefit enormously from the additional insulation cellular shades provide. iL Progetto offers single, double, and triple-cell options with top-down/bottom-up operation for flexible privacy management. Call (858) 338-1678 for a free energy consultation.`,

  'poway:roman-shades': `Poway's established Old Poway and Garden Road neighborhoods have a warmth to their interiors — wood floors, painted millwork, and family rooms that have been finished with care over decades — that deserves a window treatment with equivalent presence. Roman shades fold into tailored horizontal pleats when raised and hang as a structured flat panel when lowered, bringing real fabric and design intention to windows that a simple roller shade would underserve. For Poway's west-facing rooms, iL Progetto recommends adding a UV-blocking lining regardless of face fabric — 95–105°F summer afternoons generate enough solar radiation to fade upholstery through even a medium-weight fabric without protection. Hundreds of designer fabrics available. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'poway:wood-aluminum-blinds': `Poway's ranch homes from the 1970s and '80s have a consistent window vocabulary — double-hung or sliding windows with wood trim that pairs naturally with real wood or premium faux wood blinds. The ladder-cord tilt mechanism delivers more precise angle control than any shade, letting you direct Poway's intense summer sun toward the ceiling for indirect light rather than straight into the room. Old Poway and Garden Road homes often have multiple windows in a single room that face different directions; blinds allow you to set each independently for exactly the right balance. iL Progetto recommends faux wood for west-facing rooms subject to sustained thermal cycling. Every blind is custom-cut — call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'poway:shangri-la-shades': `Poway's Silverset and Twin Peaks communities include beautifully appointed two-story homes whose great rooms and primary suites deserve window treatments that match the interior investment. Shangri-La shades — with horizontal fabric vanes suspended between two sheer facings — bring genuine visual depth and refined light control to those rooms. When the vanes are open, diffused coastal light fills the space warmly; when tilted closed against Poway's intense summer afternoon sun, the shade provides full privacy and significant UV reduction. The motorized option is particularly compelling in Poway where automated afternoon positioning can reduce cooling load during peak heat hours. iL Progetto installs and programs motorized Shangri-La shades with same-day configuration. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'poway:curtains-drapery': `In Old Poway's established ranch homes and the larger two-story builds on Garden Road, custom drapery is the finishing layer that separates a carefully decorated room from a truly complete one. Floor-to-ceiling panels in a quality linen or velvet add acoustic warmth to rooms that hard flooring and high ceilings tend to make echo-heavy. For Poway's west-facing rooms, iL Progetto integrates UV-blocking blackout lining behind any decorative front fabric — the blackout layer does its work invisibly while the face fabric faces your room in whatever color or texture you choose. Poway summers make thermal lining a functional specification, not just a comfort upgrade. Every panel is fabricated to your exact ceiling height. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'poway:motorized-shading': `Poway's dramatic daily temperature swing — cool mornings giving way to 95–105°F afternoons and back again — creates a genuinely different set of window treatment positions for morning, midday, and evening. Managing that manually across a ranch home with six or eight windows is not a realistic task for a busy household. Motorized shading on a programmed daily schedule solves this without any ongoing effort: shades deploy at 11 a.m. ahead of peak heat, adjust at 3 p.m. as the sun angle shifts, and retract at sunset for evening ventilation. iL Progetto installs motorized systems in Silverset, Twin Peaks, and all Poway neighborhoods with Alexa, Google Home, and HomeKit integration. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'poway:plantation-shutters': `Plantation shutters are arguably the most practical long-term window treatment investment in Poway. Unlike fabric treatments that fade, warp, or require replacement after sustained exposure to 100°F+ summer heat, custom hardwood and composite shutters are rated for decades of use in exactly these conditions. Wide 4.5-inch louvres tilt to redirect Poway's punishing afternoon sun toward the ceiling for indirect light, or close completely for full privacy and maximum heat blocking. In Garden Road and Old Poway, shutters also add resale value as a permanent home improvement — a distinction that matters in Poway's competitive market. iL Progetto's shutters are custom-built to your window dimensions and installed by our licensed team (CA License #1127055). Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'poway:faux-wood-blinds': `Poway's summers subject west and south-facing windows to sustained thermal cycling that warps real wood blinds within a few seasons. Faux wood composite blinds are the durable answer: dimensionally stable at temperatures that routinely exceed 100°F, UV-resistant, and moisture-proof for bathrooms and kitchens. In Twin Peaks and Silverset homes where the ranch aesthetic pairs naturally with warm wood tones, faux wood blinds in golden oak or espresso coordinate seamlessly while outlasting anything that contains actual wood fiber. iL Progetto custom-cuts every blind to your window dimensions and offers 2-inch and 2.5-inch slat widths depending on window scale. Cordless operation recommended for child safety. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'poway:aluminum-blinds': `Poway's mix of 1970s–'80s ranch homes and newer builds in Silverset creates a range of window treatment needs, and not every window calls for a premium solution. Home offices, garages, utility rooms, and rental properties across Garden Road and Old Poway benefit from custom aluminum blinds — affordable, precise light control in a powder-coated metal slat that resists Poway's UV without fading or warping. The slim 1-inch profile stacks completely flat when fully raised, leaving windows unobstructed. iL Progetto cuts aluminum blinds to your exact dimensions in dozens of matte and metallic finishes. Cordless options available. Call (858) 338-1678 for a quote that covers every window in your Poway home.`,

  'poway:vertical-blinds': `Poway ranch homes were built with sliding glass door access to the backyard as a defining feature — a living room that opens to the patio is the architectural heart of the neighborhood. Vertical blinds remain the most practical solution for those wide openings: louvres stack completely clear when the door is in use and tilt to any angle for privacy and light management when closed. Modern fabric louvres in linen and textured weaves look nothing like the dated vinyl versions — they integrate naturally with the warm-toned interiors common in Old Poway and Garden Road. For Poway's sustained afternoon heat, a room-darkening fabric louvre makes a meaningful difference in indoor comfort. iL Progetto measures and installs across Poway. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'poway:panel-track-blinds': `The open-plan great rooms that dominate Silverset and Twin Peaks two-story builds often feature window runs of eight feet or more — proportions where individual blinds or shades start to feel visually fragmented. Panel track blinds treat the opening as a single composition: wide fabric panels traverse on an overhead rail, presenting a clean, gallery-like facade when closed and stacking fully to one side when the room is in use. In Poway's sun-intense environment, a light-filtering panel track fabric reduces afternoon glare across the entire window wall simultaneously, which is more effective than adjusting multiple individual treatments. Motorized track option available. iL Progetto serves all Poway neighborhoods. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'poway:woven-wood-shades': `Old Poway's ranch homes and the mature neighborhoods along Garden Road have interiors that lean toward warmth — wood floors, earth-toned walls, and organic materials that connect the home to the surrounding inland landscape. Woven wood shades in bamboo, jute, or sea grass extend that vocabulary to the windows, filtering Poway's intense summer light through an organic weave that throws warm, dappled patterns rather than blocking the sun mechanically. For bedrooms and west-facing rooms where privacy matters, iL Progetto adds a fabric lining behind the natural weave that increases opacity without compromising the material's texture or character. Every shade is custom-measured. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'poway:sheer-shades': `Poway's bright inland light is unmoderated by the marine layer that softens coastal San Diego — which makes sheer shades particularly effective as a first-line treatment for living rooms and home offices that need to remain bright and connected to the outdoors while eliminating the hard-edged glare of direct inland sun. The scattered diffusion that a sheer fabric provides is more comfortable for screen-heavy activities than either an unprotected window or a room-darkening shade. In Silverset and Twin Peaks homes where great rooms face multiple directions, sheer shades work across all exposures without making any room feel darker than it should. iL Progetto installs custom sheer shades in Poway with cordless and motorized lift options. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'poway:blackout-curtains': `Poway's summer days start early and bright — sunrise arrives before 5:30 a.m. in June, and without genuine blackout coverage in the bedroom, that light finds its way through even the densest room-darkening shade. iL Progetto's custom blackout curtains use triple-pass blackout lining fabricated behind any designer face fabric, creating a window treatment that eliminates light completely rather than reducing it. For the north-facing guest rooms and east-facing primary suites common in Twin Peaks and Silverset homes, blackout curtains also provide acoustic insulation that improves sleep quality independently of light control. Every panel is custom-cut to your ceiling height. Call (858) 338-1678 — free in-home consultation across Poway.`,

  'poway:sheer-drapes': `Garden Road and Old Poway homes with formal dining rooms and living rooms that see natural light throughout the day are natural candidates for sheer drapery — not as a privacy tool, but as a light management layer that makes rooms feel larger, warmer, and more refined. Fine linen or voile panels at ceiling height add visual length to rooms that standard-height blinds cut off at the window frame, and diffuse Poway's intense inland UV into the kind of scattered glow that makes everything in the room look better. iL Progetto fabricates sheer drapes to your exact ceiling height and installs on precision ripple-fold track for smooth, consistent operation. Layering a solar roller behind is recommended for afternoon heat management. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'poway:motorized-exterior': `The single most effective way to keep a Poway home cool on a 105°F afternoon is to stop solar heat before it crosses the glass — and that is exactly what motorized exterior shades do. Mounted on the outside of windows and doors, these commercial-grade mesh screens deploy on a schedule or at the touch of a button, cutting interior temperatures by up to 15 degrees before the air conditioning even engages. iL Progetto specifies UV-stable fabrics and powder-coated aluminum hardware for Poway's extreme summer conditions, with wind sensors for automatic retraction during high-wind events. The return on cooling cost savings in Silverset and Twin Peaks homes makes exterior shades one of the most financially defensible window treatment investments available. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'poway:sun-screens': `Poway sits well inland of the coast, which means the UV index is unfiltered and the afternoon sun hits living room and bedroom windows with a directness that coastal San Diego homeowners don't fully appreciate until they move inland. Solar sun screen shades address this without sacrificing views: the precision mesh fabric in Garden Road and Old Poway homes blocks 75–85% of solar heat gain while preserving a clear outward sightline to the surrounding hills and mature landscaping. At 5% openness — the most popular specification — you maintain full view clarity from inside while people outside see only a subtle mesh surface. iL Progetto carries 1%, 3%, 5%, and 10% openness fabrics. Call (858) 338-1678 for a free assessment.`,

  'poway:awnings': `Poway's outdoor living season runs essentially year-round, but the summer months from June through September require shade infrastructure to make a backyard patio genuinely usable during the day. A motorized retractable awning over the patio of an Old Poway or Garden Road ranch home can reduce the surface temperature under the awning by up to 20°F, making afternoon barbecues and weekend gatherings comfortable when they would otherwise be impossible. Commercial-grade Sunbrella fabric handles Poway's sustained UV without fading, and the aluminum arm mechanism retracts in seconds when not needed. iL Progetto installs custom awnings across Poway with wind sensor automation for protection during afternoon thermal gusts. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  // ─── CARLSBAD ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  'carlsbad:roller-shades': `Bressi Ranch and Aviara are HOA communities with specific standards for exterior window treatment appearance — colors, materials, and finish types that must coordinate with the community architectural palette. iL Progetto has navigated dozens of Carlsbad HOA approvals and knows exactly which roller shade cassette colors and fabric facings have been accepted in each community. Beyond compliance, Carlsbad's coastal salt air degrades standard roller hardware faster than inland installations — we specify stainless steel and marine-grade hardware on every coastal installation as a default, not an upgrade. Custom solar mesh and light-filtering fabrics block the persistent coastal UV without affecting views. Call (858) 338-1678 for a free consultation that covers HOA requirements upfront.`,

  'carlsbad:zebra-shades': `La Costa's established neighborhoods mix Spanish tile roofs with lush landscaping — interiors here tend toward warm neutrals, warm wood tones, and a California-casual design sensibility that zebra shades fit naturally. The alternating sheer and solid bands allow La Costa living rooms to stay connected to the mature backyard gardens while giving residents precise control over how much direct coastal light enters at any given hour. Carlsbad's HOA communities regulate exterior-visible treatments, so iL Progetto verifies HOA color and material compliance before fabrication — saving clients the delay of a rejected submittal. Every shade is custom-measured and installed by our own licensed team. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'carlsbad:cellular-shades': `Carlsbad Village's older California bungalows sit closer to the ocean than any other neighborhood in the city, which means salt air concentration is at its highest and window hardware corrosion is a real operational concern over a 10-year horizon. Cellular shades address both the energy performance challenge and the salt-air durability question: the honeycomb fabric itself is salt-air resistant, and iL Progetto specifies marine-grade cordless hardware and stainless mounting brackets for every Carlsbad Village installation. The energy benefit — trapping a thermal air buffer between glass and interior — reduces cooling load during Carlsbad's warm summer afternoons when the marine layer clears. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'carlsbad:roman-shades': `Aviara's luxury homes and La Costa's established estates have interior design investments that deserve a window treatment built to the same standard. Roman shades fold into precise horizontal pleats when raised and hang as a structured panel when lowered — the tailored, architectural quality that flat shades and blinds cannot replicate. For Carlsbad HOA communities, iL Progetto selects face fabrics in the neutral palettes that Bressi Ranch, Aviara, and La Costa review boards consistently approve, so the interior design choice and the exterior compliance work together rather than against each other. UV-blocking lining is standard on all Carlsbad Roman shades given the coastal UV exposure. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'carlsbad:wood-aluminum-blinds': `Salt air is the enemy of wood — in Carlsbad Village and the beachfront homes near the Carlsbad State Beach, the combination of moisture and salt accelerates the deterioration of any untreated wood surface. For Carlsbad homeowners who want the warmth of wood slat blinds without the coastal durability risk, iL Progetto recommends premium faux wood in this product category. The composite slats are completely impervious to salt air and humidity, and tilt to any angle for precise light control on Carlsbad's west-facing rooms. HOA communities in Bressi Ranch and Aviara have specific exterior-visible color requirements that our team checks before any fabrication order is placed. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'carlsbad:shangri-la-shades': `Aviara's oceanview homes and La Costa's hillside estates are among the most architecturally refined addresses in Carlsbad, and their window treatments need to match. Shangri-La shades — with their suspended horizontal vanes creating visual depth between two sheer fabric facings — bring museum-quality light diffusion to rooms where glare off the ocean surface or the afternoon coastal sun makes ordinary windows nearly unusable. When the vanes are open, the room fills with the soft, even light that coastal living promises; when tilted closed, the shade provides complete privacy against evening backlit windows. iL Progetto installs motorized Shangri-La shades in Carlsbad with same-day programming. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'carlsbad:curtains-drapery': `Carlsbad's HOA communities — particularly Bressi Ranch and Aviara — regulate the exterior appearance of window treatments in a way that gives homeowners less design freedom than they might expect. Floor-to-ceiling drapery is one of the treatments that requires the most careful exterior fabric selection: the lining color, visible from the street, must fall within the community-approved palette. iL Progetto has the experience to design custom drapery that satisfies HOA exterior standards while delivering exactly the interior aesthetic the homeowner wants — the two are not mutually exclusive when specifications are handled correctly from the start. Every Carlsbad drapery installation includes HOA documentation preparation. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'carlsbad:motorized-shading': `Carlsbad's coastal HOA communities increasingly specify motorized shading systems in new construction because automated treatments reduce the need for residents to manually adjust exterior-visible window coverings — a practical benefit that also keeps the community's street appearance consistent throughout the day. For existing homes in Bressi Ranch, La Costa, and Aviara, retrofitting motorized shading is straightforward with battery motors that require no electrical work and no permits. iL Progetto handles HOA compliance documentation for every motorized installation and integrates with Alexa, Google Home, and Apple HomeKit. Daily schedules that deploy shades during peak coastal UV hours and retract them at sunset are configured during the installation appointment — you leave with a working system, not an app to figure out later. Salt-air-rated hardware is standard for all Carlsbad installs. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'carlsbad:plantation-shutters': `Plantation shutters are consistently among the window treatments most readily approved by Carlsbad's HOA architectural review boards. The classic white or off-white painted shutter reads as a traditional, community-appropriate exterior element that satisfies even the most detailed Bressi Ranch and Aviara CC&Rs. Beyond HOA compliance, shutters are among the most salt-air-durable treatments available — the painted composite frame resists coastal corrosion indefinitely where fabric and cord systems degrade. iL Progetto manages the full HOA documentation process for Carlsbad shutter installations, and our custom shutters are built to your exact window dimensions rather than trimmed from a standard size. CA License #1127055. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'carlsbad:faux-wood-blinds': `Carlsbad's persistent coastal humidity — even on days when the temperature feels mild — is enough to warp real wood blinds in oceanfront and near-ocean homes over a few seasons. Faux wood blinds are the coastal-appropriate alternative: composite construction that doesn't absorb moisture, UV-stable finish that doesn't yellow under coastal sun, and a matte wood-grain appearance that satisfies HOA exterior review in Bressi Ranch and Aviara communities. The 2-inch and 2.5-inch slat profiles tilt smoothly to manage Carlsbad's coastal glare without the operational issues that humidity causes in genuine wood. iL Progetto custom-cuts every blind to your window dimensions. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'carlsbad:aluminum-blinds': `Carlsbad Village's older bungalows and the commercial-residential mixed properties near State Street include windows that call for a practical, affordable treatment rather than a premium custom finish. Powder-coated aluminum blinds are purpose-built for coastal environments — the metal construction is completely impervious to the salt air that Carlsbad Village receives daily from its proximity to the ocean, and the powder coating resists UV-driven yellowing indefinitely. iL Progetto custom-cuts aluminum blinds to your exact window dimensions in dozens of matte and metallic finishes. Cordless options are available and recommended for properties with children. HOA exterior color compliance checked on all Carlsbad orders. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'carlsbad:vertical-blinds': `La Costa's homes with south-facing great rooms and the wide glass sliders common in Carlsbad's 1990s and 2000s construction rely on vertical blinds to manage the transition between indoor and outdoor living. Contemporary fabric louvres in neutral linen weaves satisfy both the homeowner's interior design intent and the HOA exterior appearance standards that La Costa and Bressi Ranch enforce. iL Progetto verifies HOA-approved louvre colors before fabrication on every Carlsbad order, and specifies marine-grade headrail hardware to handle the salt-air environment that corrodes standard components. Every installation is sized to your exact sliding door or window opening. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'carlsbad:panel-track-blinds': `The contemporary master-planned homes in Bressi Ranch and Aviara feature large window walls and open floor plans that make panel track blinds a natural architectural fit. Wide fabric panels traverse on an overhead rail, covering a 12-foot window wall as a single composed element rather than a row of individual blinds — the result looks designed rather than functional, which matters in communities where HOA exterior review considers the visual character of window treatments. Unlike vertical blinds with their individual louvres, panel tracks present a clean, seamless face of fabric that reads as intentional interior design from both inside and outside. iL Progetto selects exterior-facing panel fabrics in HOA-compliant neutral tones for every Carlsbad installation and prepares documentation for Bressi Ranch and Aviara board submittal. Motorized track is available for fully automated operation. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'carlsbad:woven-wood-shades': `La Costa's mature eucalyptus and palm-lined streets create a California landscape backdrop that woven wood shades extend into the interior naturally. Bamboo and jute weaves filter Carlsbad's mild coastal light through an organic texture that coordinates with the warm-toned interiors common in La Costa and Aviara homes. For HOA communities — and Carlsbad has several with detailed exterior appearance standards — iL Progetto selects exterior-facing lining materials in community-approved neutral colors, ensuring the natural weave's interior warmth doesn't conflict with street-facing requirements. Salt air has minimal effect on bamboo and sea grass in interior applications, making these genuinely durable coastal choices, not just aesthetic ones. Every shade is custom-measured to your specific window dimensions. Cordless and motorized lift options are available. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'carlsbad:sheer-shades': `Carlsbad Village's proximity to the ocean creates a particular light quality — bright, diffuse, and high in UV — that sheer shades handle better than any other treatment type. The light-scattering fabric eliminates harsh coastal glare on screens and upholstery while maintaining the luminous, connected-to-the-outdoors feel that makes Carlsbad homes desirable in the first place. For HOA communities like Bressi Ranch and Aviara, iL Progetto selects exterior-visible shade cassette and fabric colors within community-approved palettes before fabrication. Salt-air-rated hardware is standard on all Carlsbad sheer shade installations. Call (858) 338-1678 for a free consultation that covers HOA requirements alongside your design preferences.`,

  'carlsbad:blackout-curtains': `Carlsbad's early summer sunrises and year-round bright mornings make genuine blackout bedroom coverage more valuable than most coastal homeowners expect — until the first June morning when ocean-reflected light pours in before 5:30 a.m. and no off-the-shelf room-darkening shade keeps pace. iL Progetto's custom blackout curtains layer triple-pass blackout lining behind any designer face fabric, providing complete light elimination while presenting a HOA-compliant exterior appearance to the street. For Bressi Ranch, Aviara, and La Costa communities, we carry exterior-approved lining colors that satisfy each community's review board requirements. The face fabric, visible from inside your Carlsbad bedroom, can be any designer material in our collection — the blackout function happens invisibly from behind. Serving all Carlsbad neighborhoods. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'carlsbad:sheer-drapes': `Aviara's oceanview rooms and La Costa's hillside primary suites are the kind of spaces that sheer drapery was made for — floor-to-ceiling linen panels that frame a view without blocking it, diffusing coastal light into a warm glow that flatters every surface in the room. For HOA communities, the exterior-facing lining color requires coordination with community-approved palettes, a step iL Progetto handles during the consultation before any fabric is ordered. Precision ripple-fold track installation ensures the panels move smoothly and consistently across wide openings. Pairs naturally with a solar roller shade for afternoon heat management on west-facing windows. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'carlsbad:motorized-exterior': `Carlsbad's persistent coastal UV is lower in intensity than Poway's but longer in duration — cloud cover burns off by mid-morning most days, and western exposure windows take sun from roughly 11 a.m. until sunset. Motorized exterior shades stop that solar energy before it crosses the glass, reducing indoor temperatures without requiring air conditioning to compensate. For HOA communities in Bressi Ranch and Aviara, iL Progetto selects exterior fabric colors and cassette finishes within community-approved palettes and prepares HOA submittal documentation. All hardware is marine-grade rated for Carlsbad's salt-air environment. Wind sensor automation included on all Carlsbad exterior shade installations. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'carlsbad:sun-screens': `Carlsbad's coastal homes — particularly in La Costa and Carlsbad Village — sit in a light environment that is simultaneously bright, UV-intense, and glare-producing off the ocean surface. Solar sun screen shades address all three without sacrificing views: the precision mesh fabric at 5% openness blocks 75–85% of solar heat gain while preserving clear sightlines from inside the home. For HOA communities, iL Progetto selects screen fabric colors within Bressi Ranch, Aviara, and La Costa community-approved palettes. Marine-grade headrail hardware is standard for every Carlsbad installation. Motorized lift with wind sensor automation is recommended. Call (858) 338-1678 for a free site assessment.`,

  'carlsbad:awnings': `Carlsbad's year-round outdoor living culture and mild coastal temperatures make retractable awnings a practical investment that extends patio use well beyond what the climate already permits on its own. In HOA communities like Bressi Ranch and Aviara, awning fabric color and hardware finish are typically subject to architectural review — a step that surprises homeowners who haven't navigated a Carlsbad CC&R process before. iL Progetto prepares all HOA documentation and works exclusively within community-approved Sunbrella fabric palettes, so approval is secured well before installation day. Commercial-grade aluminum arm mechanisms handle the coastal afternoon sea breezes Carlsbad regularly experiences. Wind sensors are standard on all our Carlsbad awning installations, providing automatic retraction when gusts exceed safe operational thresholds. Call (858) 338-1678 to begin your free design consultation.`,

  // ─── LA JOLLA ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  'la-jolla:roller-shades': `La Jolla Shores homes built on the bluff edge face a specific optical problem that most window treatment specifications miss: the reflective surface of the Pacific Ocean amplifies incoming glare by as much as 30% compared to standard coastal exposure. A solar mesh roller shade at 3–5% openness cuts that glare to a workable level while preserving the ocean view that makes these properties worth owning. iL Progetto specifies marine-grade stainless hardware for every La Jolla installation — the salt-air environment at bluff-top elevations degrades standard components noticeably within two or three seasons. HOA and Coastal Commission documentation support included. Call (858) 338-1678 for a free site assessment.`,

  'la-jolla:zebra-shades': `Bird Rock's mid-century homes sit on lots where the street-side and ocean-side windows serve completely different functions — privacy from the sidewalk on one side, view preservation with glare management on the other. Zebra shades handle both exposures from the same product category: on the ocean side, the sheer bands preserve views while the opaque bands cut glare at peak afternoon angles; on the street side, aligning the opaque bands provides complete privacy without darkening the room. iL Progetto carries zebra shades in the neutral white and greige tones consistently approved by Bird Rock and La Jolla HOA review boards. Marine-grade hardware standard. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'la-jolla:cellular-shades': `The floor-to-ceiling glass walls common in La Jolla Shores and Mt. Soledad contemporary homes create a thermal management challenge that their heating and cooling systems were not necessarily designed to handle alone. Cellular honeycomb shades add meaningful insulation value at the glass plane — the hexagonal air pockets trap thermal energy that would otherwise radiate directly into living spaces on afternoon west and south exposures. For La Jolla homes subject to Coastal Commission design review, iL Progetto selects exterior-facing shade colors in the neutral tones the commission consistently approves, and prepares all documentation required for the submittal process. Double-cell construction recommended for direct-ocean-facing windows. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'la-jolla:roman-shades': `La Jolla's luxury interior market demands window treatments that function at the same design level as the rest of the home. In Village homes and Bird Rock's carefully restored mid-century properties, Roman shades in Belgian linen, silk blends, or designer textile bring architectural weight and material quality to windows that a roller shade would underperform. iL Progetto's Roman shade program includes hundreds of fabrics from premium vendors, with UV-blocking lining integrated as a standard specification for La Jolla installations given the ocean-amplified UV exposure. Every shade is custom-fabricated to your window dimensions. For HOA communities, exterior lining colors are pre-verified before any fabric order. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'la-jolla:wood-aluminum-blinds': `La Jolla's bluff-top homes experience a salt-air concentration that is among the highest in San Diego County — a fact that argues against real wood in direct-ocean-facing rooms. For homes in Windansea and La Jolla Shores where aesthetic preference runs toward warm wood tones, iL Progetto recommends premium faux wood blinds: the composite material is completely impervious to the salt-air environment and delivers the same ladder-cord tilt precision as real wood at any angle. Mt. Soledad homes away from the immediate bluff typically handle real wood well, particularly in HVAC-controlled interior rooms. HOA color approval checked prior to fabrication on all La Jolla orders. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'la-jolla:shangri-la-shades': `La Jolla's architecture magazine-caliber interiors — the glass-wall contemporaries of La Jolla Shores, the mid-century estates on Mt. Soledad — demand window treatments that contribute to the design rather than merely serving it. Shangri-La shades, with floating horizontal vanes suspended between two sheer facings, create the kind of interior light quality that professional interior designers specify for their most demanding projects: diffused, luminous, and visually deep rather than flat. The motorized vane tilt adjusts automatically to manage the ocean glare that shifts across the day as La Jolla's sun angle changes from morning to afternoon. iL Progetto programs motorized Shangri-La systems with full smart home integration. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'la-jolla:curtains-drapery': `Custom drapery in La Jolla's luxury residences is a material and fabrication specification at a level that only bespoke work can satisfy. Floor-to-ceiling panels in Belgian linen, raw silk, or performance velvet — fabricated to your exact ceiling height, installed on precision ceiling-mounted ripple-fold track — are a fundamentally different object from catalog drapery. iL Progetto sources fabric from premium vendors, handles HOA and Coastal Commission exterior lining color compliance, and installs on precision metal track systems that operate without binding or sagging across 12-foot and wider openings. La Jolla homes from The Village to La Jolla Shores are in our regular service area. Call (858) 338-1678 for a design consultation.`,

  'la-jolla:motorized-shading': `Homes in La Jolla Shores and on Mt. Soledad's ocean-facing slopes manage light that changes character dramatically from morning to evening — cool blue marine-layer diffusion at 8 a.m., intense direct glare by noon, warm raking light at 4 p.m. Managing that manually across a home with floor-to-ceiling glass walls is impractical. Motorized shading on scene-based programming lets you define positions for each condition and trigger them by voice, scheduled time, or ambient light sensor. iL Progetto integrates with Lutron, Control4, HomeKit, and all major smart home platforms. La Jolla's HOA and Coastal Commission requirements are addressed during the design phase. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'la-jolla:plantation-shutters': `Plantation shutters are the default standard in La Jolla's luxury residential market — favored by HOA boards, Coastal Commission reviewers, and interior designers alike for their permanent, architecturally integrated appearance. Custom composite or hardwood shutters built to your exact window dimensions become part of the home's architecture rather than a furnishing, which is the distinction that matters when La Jolla property values are at stake. Wide 4.5-inch louvres manage the intense ocean glare common in Windansea and La Jolla Shores homes, and the painted white or off-white frame satisfies essentially every HOA exterior appearance requirement in the community. iL Progetto manages all documentation. CA License #1127055. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'la-jolla:faux-wood-blinds': `La Jolla's coastal elevation means even interior rooms receive meaningful salt-air exposure through window operation over a decade-long horizon. For Bird Rock and Windansea homes where window treatments are changed infrequently and expected to perform for years, faux wood composite blinds are the durable coastal specification: no moisture absorption, no warping under thermal cycling, and no salt-air corrosion of the slat surface. The warm wood-grain finish in off-white, golden, or espresso tones coordinates naturally with La Jolla's interior design aesthetic. HOA-compliant exterior colors pre-verified before every order. iL Progetto installs with marine-grade hardware across all La Jolla neighborhoods. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'la-jolla:aluminum-blinds': `Aluminum blinds find their role in La Jolla in utility rooms, home offices, secondary bedrooms, and rental units in properties where practical durability and light control matter more than premium aesthetics. Powder-coated aluminum is one of the most salt-air-resistant materials available for a window treatment, which makes it a genuinely appropriate coastal choice in La Jolla — not a compromise. Unlike wood or fabric treatments that absorb the salt-laden moisture common in Bird Rock and La Jolla Shores, powder-coated aluminum is chemically inert to the coastal environment. iL Progetto custom-cuts aluminum blinds to your exact window dimensions in matte white, silver, and champagne finishes that coordinate with La Jolla's light interior palettes. Cordless lift is standard on all our La Jolla installations. HOA exterior color compliance verified before every fabrication order. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'la-jolla:vertical-blinds': `La Jolla's bluff-top luxury homes frequently feature 8-foot-wide sliding glass doors that open to ocean-view terraces — precisely the opening that vertical blinds were engineered to cover. The louvres stack completely clear of the door track when fully open, leaving the ocean view and the terrace access completely unobstructed. For La Jolla's HOA communities, iL Progetto specifies fabric louvre colors within community-approved palettes and uses marine-grade headrail hardware designed for salt-air environments. A fabric louvre with a solar mesh weave allows views through the glass even when the treatment is closed — the right specification for ocean-facing doors. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'la-jolla:panel-track-blinds': `The floor-to-ceiling glass walls characteristic of La Jolla Shores and Mt. Soledad contemporary homes are the architectural expression that panel track blinds address most elegantly. Wide fabric panels on an overhead rail cover a 14-foot glass wall as a single composed surface — no individual slats or louvres to fragment the view of the panel treatment when closed, no visual clutter when stacked open. For La Jolla HOA communities, exterior-facing panel fabrics are selected within approved neutral palettes, and Coastal Commission documentation is prepared where required. Motorized track is standard on most La Jolla panel track installations. Call (858) 338-1678 for a design consultation.`,

  'la-jolla:woven-wood-shades': `La Jolla's biophilic design community — particularly the interior designers working in Bird Rock and The Village — frequently specifies woven wood shades in bamboo and jute for primary suites and informal living rooms where organic materials reinforce the connection to the Pacific landscape. The natural weave filters coastal light into warm, dappled patterns that artificial materials cannot replicate. For La Jolla HOA communities, exterior-facing lining materials are selected in community-approved neutral colors. Salt air has minimal impact on bamboo and sea grass in interior applications — these are durable coastal choices that age gracefully in La Jolla's environment. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'la-jolla:sheer-shades': `Ocean glare in La Jolla is a different category of problem than ordinary sunlight — the reflective Pacific surface amplifies incoming light by a significant margin, turning oceanfront rooms into something close to unwatchable in the afternoon without treatment. Sheer shades scatter that intensity across the room in diffused, even illumination that makes the space livable without closing the view. The key specification for La Jolla is the sheer fabric's UV transmission factor — iL Progetto carries fabrics that block up to 78% of UV in the sheer position, protecting valuable art, rugs, and furnishings throughout La Jolla Shores and Windansea homes. Marine-grade hardware standard. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'la-jolla:blackout-curtains': `La Jolla's primary bedrooms in oceanfront homes face a counterintuitive problem: the very orientation that makes them worth owning — the west-facing ocean view — makes them the hardest rooms to sleep in during summer when direct Pacific light floods in at dawn and early morning. Triple-pass blackout curtains behind a sheer layer or solar roller provide complete room darkening for sleep while preserving the view treatment during waking hours. iL Progetto fabricates blackout drapery in designer face fabrics — Belgian linen, performance velvet, embroidered panels — with HOA-compliant exterior lining colors. Every panel is fabricated to your exact ceiling-to-floor dimension. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'la-jolla:sheer-drapes': `The living rooms and dining rooms of La Jolla's luxury homes — from The Village's Spanish Colonial estates to La Jolla Shores' glass-wall contemporaries — command window treatments that read as part of the interior design investment, not an afterthought. Floor-to-ceiling sheer drapery in fine Belgian linen or silk voile creates the luminous, layered light quality that interior designers specify for rooms of this caliber: not blocking, not darkening, but sculpting the incoming ocean light into something beautiful. iL Progetto custom-fabricates sheer drapes to your exact dimensions, installs on precision ceiling-mounted track, and handles HOA exterior lining color compliance. Call (858) 338-1678 for a design consultation at your La Jolla home.`,

  'la-jolla:motorized-exterior': `La Jolla's ocean-facing homes are among the most thermally challenging in San Diego County: bluff-top elevation eliminates any shading from surrounding structures, the reflective Pacific amplifies incoming solar radiation, and the views that make the homes extraordinary also make interior shading difficult. Motorized exterior shades are the only treatment that addresses the heat before it crosses the glass — reducing interior temperatures by up to 15 degrees before the air conditioning engages. iL Progetto specifies commercial-grade, marine-rated hardware and UV-stable mesh fabric for every La Jolla exterior installation, and manages Coastal Commission documentation where ocean-facing shade systems require review. Wind sensor automation is standard. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'la-jolla:sun-screens': `At bluff-top elevation in La Jolla Shores and Windansea, the sun screen specification matters more than almost anywhere else in San Diego County. The combination of direct Pacific UV, ocean surface reflection, and elevated exposure means that interior surfaces, artwork, and furnishings are under sustained radiation pressure for most of the day. A 5% openness solar screen fabric blocks up to 85% of that energy while maintaining the ocean view that La Jolla homeowners protect above all else. iL Progetto carries mesh fabrics in the neutral color palette that La Jolla HOA review boards and the Coastal Commission consistently accept, with marine-grade hardware and motorized operation standard. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'la-jolla:awnings': `La Jolla's oceanfront terraces and bluff-top patios are among the most valuable outdoor spaces in Southern California, and they are also among the most sun-exposed. A motorized retractable awning over a La Jolla Shores or Mt. Soledad terrace can reduce the surface temperature under the awning by up to 20°F and cut glare intensity enough to make afternoon outdoor use genuinely comfortable. For HOA communities and Coastal Commission-regulated properties, iL Progetto selects Sunbrella fabric colors and hardware finishes within approved palettes and prepares all documentation before installation. Commercial-grade aluminum arm mechanisms handle the coastal wind loads typical of La Jolla's elevated sites. Call (858) 338-1678.`,
}


